      "instruction": "<p>Reboil half a kettle</p><p>Once the onion has started to soften, add<strong> half</strong> of the<strong> chopped garlic</strong> (save the rest for later!) to the pan with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Add 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[425ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> with your<strong> vegetable stock mix </strong>and <strong>soft cheese</strong></p><p>Add the juice of <strong>half</strong> your<strong> lemon[s] </strong>and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong>, then give everything a good mix up and cook for 3-4 min or until thickened</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
